target: map
validations:
  - name: grid_renders_correctly
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the tile grid is visible on the canvas. The map should
        display as a 40x30 grid of tiles. Grass tiles should be the default
        fill. The entrance tile at the bottom-center should be visually
        distinct from regular grass tiles. Tile boundaries should be
        discernible so the player can identify individual grid cells.
  - name: tile_placement_works
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that the player can place path and water tiles on the map.
        Selecting a tile type from the build menu and clicking on a grass
        tile should change that tile's type. The new tile should render with
        the correct visual style. Tiles that are occupied by an enclosure
        should reject placement attempts.
  - name: pathfinding_functional
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that A* pathfinding works correctly. When a path of connected
        walkable tiles exists between the entrance and an enclosure, visitors
        should be able to navigate to it. If no walkable route exists (e.g.,
        the path is blocked), visitors should not teleport or get stuck in
        walls — they should either wait or leave. The pathfinding should
        handle edge cases like the destination being adjacent to the
        entrance without errors.
